  <metadata>
    <id>MicroLite.Extensions.WebApi.OData4</id>
    <version>0.0.0</version>
    <authors>Trevor Pilley and MicroLite Project Contributors</authors>
    <owners>Trevor Pilley</owners>
    <description>An extension for the MicroLite ORM Framework to add OData 4.0 query support to MicroLite.Extensions.WebApi.</description>
    <releaseNotes>See https://github.com/TrevorPilley/MicroLite.Extensions.WebApi/releases for a summary of changes made in this release of the package.

Net.Http.WebApi.OData 4.0.0 changes:
- Removed types/members obsoleted in 3.4.x and earlier
- Expression QueryNode objects refactored (partly for performance, partly to simplify)
- Improved validation
- Fixed parsing of DateTimeOffset
- Correctly returning HTTP 400 and HTTP 501 where appropriate instead of ODataException which resulted in HTTP 500
- SelectQueryOption and ExpandQueryOption merged into SelectExpandQueryOption since they have the same implementation
- Introduction of EdmProperty which is used in SelectExpandQueryOption, OrderByProperty, PropertyAccessNode
- The InlineCount&lt;T&gt; class was still returning OData 2.0 format { "__count":0, "results":[] }, updated to OData 4.0 format { "@odata.count":0, "value":[] } replaced by PagedResult&lt;T&gt; class
- SubStringOf removed
- Contains added
- DateTime &amp; Time removed
- Date and TimeOfDay added (don't require prefixing)
- DateTimeOffset parsing improved, also doesn't require prefix
- Guid doesn't require prefix
- $inlinecount=allpages replaced by $count=true
- Added $search query option
- Added FractionalSeconds, Now, MinDateTime and MaxDateTime functions
</releaseNotes>
